<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910219-0157</DOCNO><DOCID>910219-0157.</DOCID><HL>   Hurco 1st-Period Net Plunged</HL><DATE>02/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   HURC</CO><IN>FACTORY EQUIPMENT (FAC)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   INDIANAPOLIS -- Hurco Cos., citing the effect ofrecessions domestically and in the United Kingdom, said netincome for the fiscal first-quarter, ended Jan. 31, plunged88% to $254,000, or five cents a share, from $2,167,000, or38 cents a share, in the fiscal first quarter a year earlier.   Revenue for the period fell fractionally to $22,056,000from $22,722,000.</LP><TEXT>   The maker of computer-controlled machine tool systemsderives 65% of revenue from U.S. operations, with the restfrom overseas. Sales were strong in Germany and Asia, thecompany said, but gains in those countries weren't enough tooffset the declines domestically and in the U.K.   Second-quarter results will remain &quot;under continuedpressure,&quot; the company said.</TEXT></DOC>